	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />1. While most pages call the bit 6 and 7 of $4000/4004 as duty, the length counter page calls them sequence.
<br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Length_Counter" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Length_Counter</a>
<br />
<br />2. I followed the APU Sweep page and completely missed the point that
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">A NES APU sweep unit can be made to periodically adjust a pulse channel's period up or down. </div> means the reload flag will be set periodically. I suggest mentioning this fact in the main text below.
<br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Sweep" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Sweep</a>
<br />
<br />3. Add frame counter to the flow charts. Having 1 starting point in a flow chart makes it easier to follow.
<br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Pulse" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Pulse</a>
<br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Triangle" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Triangle</a>
<br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Noise" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Noise</a>
<br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_DMC" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_DMC</a>
<br />
<br />Thanks.

		

